description: One-shot. An angel is murdered at the hands of a demon. So bold are the agents of Hell, so convinced of their own dominion over earth, they now feel they can slay angels with impunity. The cold war between heaven and hell heats up. In response, the Archangel Michael goes on his own murderous rampage, taking down a score of demons. In the process he hears of the presence of a fallen demon of sorts. Her name is Yae-el, the Adversary. Stripped of her powers, eternal youth and beauty, she is trapped in a prison of ruined flesh and banished to earth. Michael hatches a plan to make good use of her.
name: The Adversary: Reborn

description:
In January 2013, "Mars Attacks" invades five different IDW timelines and universes in five weeks and five standalone one-shots:

  1. Mars Attacks Popeye
  2. Mars Attacks Kiss
  3. Mars Attacks the Real Ghostbusters
  4. Mars Attacks the Transformers
  5. Mars Attacks Robots vs. Zombies

Note: For each one-shot two variant covers exist. These retailer incentive variants are unrelated to the stories but feature favorite heroes from the IDW stable.

  1. Popeye (Miss Fury, Opus)
  2. Kiss (Judge Dredd, Star Slammers)
  3. Real Ghostbusters (Chew, Madman)
  4. Transformers (Spike, Strangers in Paradise)
  5. Robots vs. Zombies (Rog-2000, Cerebus)

Collected in Mars Attacks IDW.
name: Mars Attacks: Zombies vs Robots
